descript.abstract: The Census Tracts for the 2000 US Census. These boundary files are derived from the US Census Bureau's TIGER project and have been geographically modified to fit the New York City base map. Because some census tract are under water not all census tracts are contained in this file, only census tracts that are partially or totally located on land have been mapped in this file.
descript.purpose: These districts were created by the Department of City Planning to aid city agencies in administering public services.

idinfo.accconst: The data are freely available to all New York City agencies and the public.
idinfo.useconst: While all possible measures have been taken to ensure the accuracy of this data, the NYC Department of City Planning and the City of New York assume no responsibility for the accuracy of this data. All users should independently verify the accuracy of the data for their purposes.
